3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OKX calculates BONK/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a premium index methodology. The platform's portfolio margin mode allows BONK positions to share margin with other assets, reducing overall margin requirements. Funding payments occur automatically with maker fees at 0.02% and taker fees at 0.05% applying to position adjustments. OKX's API provides real-time funding rate predictions 1 hour before settlement, crucial for timing arbitrage entries."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","BONK","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BONK's meme coin nature creates extreme sentiment swings that often result in elevated funding rates, particularly during Solana ecosystem rallies or social media-driven price movements. The token's mid-tier volume on OKX provides sufficient liquidity for arbitrage while avoiding the overcrowded competition seen in major pairs. BONK's correlation with SOL price action creates predictable funding rate patterns during broader Solana market cycles."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BONK/USDT funding rates on OKX typically spike above 0.1% during meme coin rally periods, especially when social media sentiment drives retail FOMO. Negative funding rates frequently occur during broader crypto market downturns when short positions dominate. The pair shows strong correlation with GMT+8 trading hours due to significant Asian retail interest in meme tokens. Weekend funding rates tend to be more volatile due to reduced institutional participation and higher retail dominance."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OKX's portfolio margin mode enables efficient BONK funding rate arbitrage by using SOL or other Solana ecosystem tokens as cross-collateral. Long funding rate positions benefit from OKX's competitive maker rebates when building spot hedge positions. The 8-hour cycle provides ample time to establish hedged positions, particularly useful given BONK's high intraday volatility. Arbitrage opportunities are strongest during US market hours when retail sentiment diverges most from institutional positioning."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BONK's extreme volatility can quickly erode funding rate profits if spot-futures basis moves adversely, requiring tight position sizing and risk management. The token's relatively small market cap means large arbitrage positions can impact the funding rate calculation itself. OKX's portfolio margin system introduces cross-asset liquidation risks if other positions in the portfolio move against the trader. Meme coin regulatory scrutiny could lead to sudden delisting announcements, creating urgent position closure requirements."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does OKX calculate BONK/USDT funding rates?","answer":"OKX uses a premium index methodology that compares the BONK perpetual price to the spot index every 8 hours. The funding rate equals the premium/discount averaged over the 8-hour period, with a maximum rate of ±0.75% per cycle to prevent extreme payments."},{"question":"Can I use portfolio margin for BONK funding rate arbitrage on OKX?","answer":"Yes, OKX's portfolio margin mode allows BONK perpetual positions to share margin requirements with other crypto assets. This enables more capital-efficient arbitrage strategies, especially when hedging with SOL or other Solana ecosystem tokens as collateral."},{"question":"What are the minimum position sizes for BONK/USDT perpetuals on OKX?","answer":"OKX sets the minimum BONK perpetual order at 1 USDT notional value. Given BONK's low unit price, this represents millions of BONK tokens, making the pair accessible to retail arbitrage traders while maintaining sufficient precision for larger institutional positions."},{"question":"How do OKX's BONK funding rates compare to other exchanges?","answer":"OKX's 8-hour funding cycle for BONK typically shows higher volatility than Binance's similar cycle due to lower overall volume. However, OKX's portfolio margin system can make arbitrage more capital-efficient, potentially offsetting slightly less favorable base rates."}]}]
